    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like a lot of people say it was a massive strategic mistake because of the instability that followed. do you think there was actually a valid way to handle it without the chaos, or was intervention just inherently destined to fail in this case?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
