      "content": "idk, the \"more robust plan\" thing sounds kind of like an excuse for why the intervention was bad. if the end result is just a failed state and more terrorism in the region, isn't it more accurate to just call it a failure of liberal interventionism overall? like, can you even justify that kind of policy if it consistently breaks things?",
